{{see|zarna}}

==Romanian==

===Etymology===
Disputed. May be from a pre-Roman language, such as Dacian or Thracian, comparisons having been made to the Dacian name for the [[Black Hellebore]] (Latin: ''[[Helleborus niger]])'', ''[[Prodiarna]]'' (''diarna'' --> ''zârnă''). Cf. Sorin Paliga, et al. The [[W:Romanian Academy|Romanian Academy]] in its official dictionary, the ''Dicţionarul explicativ al limbii române'' (1998), however, derives the word from Common Slavic *''[[zorno]]'', "a berry" or "a grain" [http://dexonline.ro/search.php?cuv=zarna&source=].

===Noun===
'''zârnă''' {{f}} (pl. ''zârne'')

# black [[nightshade]] (''[[Solanum nigrum]]''), also known as [[sunberry]].

